.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-6-5::.
4 different games are played: mah-jongg, chess, snooker, whist
4 different brands of cigars are smoked: montecristo, old-henry, blend, dannemann
1. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left of the person playing whist##1
2. the person playing whist is somewhere to the left of the blend-smoker##5
3. the person playing whist is somewhere to the left of the old-henry-smoker##5
4. the person playing chess is not the dannemann-smoker##6
5. the montecristo-smoker is not the person playing mah-jongg##6
6. the person playing snooker is on the left of the person playing chess##1
7. the blend-smoker is on the far left or far right##3

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |  2   |    3     |   4   |
| Beverage    | mah-jongg        | whist | snooker | chess |
| Transport   | dannemann | montecristo | old-henry     | blend   |

